### **Overview**

The grey literature backlog is one of archaeology's most serious problems: thousands of excavation reports sit unwritten because the reporting workload after fieldwork is enormous. This tool accepts structured site data — context sheets, finds summaries, section drawings, sample results — and drafts a grey literature report in the standard format required by the relevant planning authority or heritage body (Historic England, Historic Environment Scotland, US Section 106, etc.). The drafter respects regional conventions and produces a document ready for researcher review and minor editing.


### **Core Functions**

- Import context sheet data (CSV, FileMaker, Ark system export)

- Import finds catalogue data

- Upload site photos, plans, and section drawings

- Select reporting standard (Historic England, HES, Irish NMS, US 106, etc.)

- AI drafts: executive summary, methodology, results by period, discussion, archive statement

- Auto-generate context index, finds concordance, and bibliography

- Highlights areas needing human specialist input

- Export as Word doc ready for submission


| **Tech Stack** | LLM with structured data ingestion, report template library by jurisdiction, document generation |
